AB  - The positive correlation between export instability and export expansion, reported by Lam in a recent paper, is shown to be the result of a bias caused by the manner in which the instability index was calculated, and by using data series which end in a year of unusually high exports. It is shown that when correction is made for these factors, there is no statistically significant correlation between export instability and export expansion or domestic income expansion.
