AB  - This note provides a comparative price analysis for traded products of India, from 1960 to 1975. Unit values of traded products between India and the industrial countries provide a benchmark. The results show very close links between unit value changes and variations in domestic prices especially in basic consumer goods and intermediaries. In contrast, unit values provide no significant explanation for price variations in most of the machinery and transport equipments.
